{
  "texts": [
    "Effective AI tools rely on high-quality, annotated data, but such data is often scarce, reducing the models' accuracy and generalizability in realworld applications.",
    "Integrating AI into existing healthcare systems can also be difficult, as the complexity of the technology and the extensive training required can overwhelm healthcare providers, slowing down adoption.",
    "Many AI models function as \"black boxes,\" making it hard for clinicians to understand the reasoning behind the decisions.",
    "This lack of transparency can undermine trust, as clinicians may be hesitant to rely on AI without clear explanations.",
    "Additionally, AI algorithms may inherit biases from their training data, resulting in unequal performance across diverse patient groups, raising ethical concerns about fairness in breast cancer care [35]."
  ]
}